acted%20buyers%20from%20other%20schools%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20graduating%20high%20school%20in%202017%2C%20Bonvicini%20continued%20to%20grow%20her%20business%20while%20attending%20the%20University%20of%20Southern%20California.%20She%20was%20still%20reworking%20vintage%20denim%2C%20often%20doing%20trunk%20shows%20to%20sell%20to%20the%20sororities%20on%20campus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20making%20cut-off%20shorts%2C%20she%20started%20adding%20details%20like%20chains%20to%20the%20vintage%20jeans%2C%20or%20sewing%20and%20combining%20scrap%20denim%20pieces%20to%20create%20something%20new%20%E2%80%94%20like%20the%20patchwork%20dress%2C%20which%20is%20made%20from%20old%20leg%20panels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20instead%20of%20pocketing%20her%20profits%2C%20she%20reinvested%20the%20cash%20into%20hiring%20PR%20experts%20who%20had%20the%20connections%20she%20didn't.%20That%20when%20things%20really%20started%20to%20pick%20up%2C%20after%20they%20started%20sending%20her%20products%20out%20to%20influencers%20and%20celebrities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20expect%20PR%20to%20work%20unless%20you%20have%20a%20great%20product%2C%26quot%3B%20Bonvicini%20said.%20%26quot%3BOtherwise%20you're%20just%20wasting%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Composite%20image%20of%20Elena%20Bonvicini%20in%20her%20LA%20showroom%2C%20and%20a%20headshot%20of%20her%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66bfeca0b4912df3ae1c7a96%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EElena%20Bonvicini's%20EB%20Denim%20showroom%20is%20downtown%20Los%20Angeles.%3Cp%3EKelsey%20Vlamis%3B%20EB%20Denim%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20first%20influencers%20to%20wear%20her%20denim%20were%20Danielle%20Bernstein%2C%20founder%20of%20blog%20and%20brand%20WeWoreWhat%2C%20and%20Chiara%20Ferragni%2C%20an%20Italian%20fashion%20influencer%20and%20blogger.%20Once