inancial%20responsibility%20is%20more%20important%20than%20%26quot%3Bimpressing%20people%20on%20social%20media.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221427%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22composite%20of%20Witter%20in%20Dubai%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66be34c7b4912df3ae1c0420%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221070%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWitter%20visited%20Dubai%20in%20May%20after%20completing%20her%20first%20year%20at%20Dalhousie%20University's%20Schulich%20School%20of%20Law.%3Cp%3ECrystal%20Witter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWitter%20funds%20her%20trips%20using%20%3Cs%3Eher%3C%2Fs%3E%20earnings%20from%20her%20TikTok%20accounts%2C%20her%20main%20source%20of%20income%2C%20which%20she%20said%20averages%20more%20than%20%246%2C000%20monthly.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E(BI%20could%20not%20verify%20this.)%20While%20she%20does%20use%20a%20travel-specific%20credit%20card%20for%20points%2C%20she%20won't%20accrue%20a%20balance%20or%20use%20buy%20now%2C%20pay%20later%20services%2C%20calling%20them%20%26quot%3Brisky.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHaving%20high%20debt%20is%20not%20the%20real%20trend%20despite%20what%20people%20see%20on%20social%20media%2C%26quot%3B%20Witter%20said.%20%26quot%3BAs%20young%20people%2C%20we%20have%20a%20responsibility%20to%20ensure%20our%20future%20is%20safe%20as%20much%20as%20we%20want%20to%20enjoy%20the%20present.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22337c5328-110e-4f89-97ab-6afa38915745%5C%22%3ETake%20it%20from%20someone%20who%20learned%20the%20hard%20way.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20there's%20one%20person%20who%20can%20speak%20to%20Witter's%20sentiments%2C%20it's%20Canada-based%20Erin%20Spencer.%20Her%20full-time%20job%20is%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Bfinancial%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20she%20also%20creates%20TikTok%20content%20about%20her%20journey%20with%20debt%2C%20a%20topic%20she's%20personally%20well-versed%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%2019%2C%20she%20was%20accruing%20credit%20card%20debt%20while%20%26quot%3Bgoing%20on%20trips%20I%20couldn't%20afford%2C%26quot%3B%20Spencer%20told%20BI.%20By%2024%2C%20she%20had%20accumulated%2025%2C000%20Canadian%20dollars%20%E2%80%94%20about%20%2418%2C300%20%E2%80%94%20in%20debt%2C%20ultimately%20filing%20for%20bankruptcy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20at%2030%2C%20she%20still%20owes%20more%20than%20CAD%2426%2C150%20%E2%80%94%20about%20%2419%2C100%20%E2%80%94%20for%20payments%20such%20as%20taxes%2C%20car%2C%20and%20student%20loans.%20%26quot%3BI've%20basically%20had%20debt%20my%20entire%20adult%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Spencer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20others%2C%20accruing%20a%20credit%20card%20balance%20was%20her%20way%20of%20affording%20trips.%20For%20example%2C%20her%20Boston%20vacation%20in%202022%20and%20an%20international%20shopping%20trip%20to%20Maine%20in%202023%2C%20which%20she%20estimates%20had%20added%20a%20%26quot%3Bcouple%20thousand%26quot%3B%20onto%20her%20card.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221825%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22photo%20of%20trader%20joes%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66be34f75da406397bf641b8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221369%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESpencer%20said%20social%20media%20influenced%20her%20to%20go%20on%20a%20cross-border%20shopping%20trip%20to%20Maine%2C%20which%20included%20visiting%20stores%20that%20aren't%20available%20in%20Canada%2C%20such%20as%20Trader%20Joe's.%3Cp%3EErin%20Spencer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20just%20because%20she%20went%20on%20these%20vacations%20doesn't%20mean%20they%20were%20stress-free.%20%26quot%3BI%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20living%20a%20lie%20and%20hiding%20something%20from%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20embarrassed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAm%20I%20really%20enjoying%20it%3F%26quot%3B%20Spencer%20recalled%20asking%20herself.%20%26quot%3BAm%20I%20trying%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20Joneses%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20is%2C%20until%20a%20switch%20flipped%20in%20November%2C%20when%20she%20shared%20her%20bankruptcy%20story%20on%20TikTok.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20she's%20wholly%20committed%20to%20paying%20off%20her%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20a%20statistic%2C%26quot%3B%20Spencer%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20get%20into%20a%20cycle%20of%20filing%20bankruptcy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20this%20mindset%20shift%2C%20she%20still%20has%20a%20goal%20of%20traveling%20once%20or%20twice%20a%20year.%20But%20instead%20of%20going%20further%20into%20debt%2C%20she%20now%20uses%20a%20sinking%20fund%2C%20which%20she%20supplies%20with%20earnings%20from%20some%20of%20her%20TikTok%20brand%20deals%20and%20about%20%2450%20to%20%24100%20from%20each%20of%20her%20corporate%20job's%20paychecks.%20(She%20said%20she%20makes%20between%20CAD%2475%2C000%20to%20CAD%2485%2C000%20annually%20from%20both.%20BI%20could%20not%20verify%20the%20amount.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20she%20still%20has%20debt%2C%20having%20a%20travel-specific%20fund%20has%20allowed%20her%20to%20truly%20enjoy%20her%20vacations%2C%20including%20her%20latest%20two-week%20%26quot%3Brecharge%26quot%3B%20trip%20in%20April%20to%20Florida%2C%20which%20cost%20about%20%242%2C500%20%E2%80%94%20but%20didn't%20deepen%20the%20well%20of%20her%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22composite%20of%20Spencer%20in%20Florida%2C%20walking%20by%20water%20and%20posing%20in%20front%20of%20it%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66be3548b4912df3ae1c04a6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESpencer%20said%20her%20Florida%20trip%20was%20likely%20the%20most%20expensive%20vacation%20she's%20taken%20in%20a%20while.%3Cp%3EErin%20Spencer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20she%20got%20some%20backlash%20on%20TikTok%20for%20going%20on%20the%20trip.%20And%20yes%2C%20she%20could've%20put%20that%20money%20toward%20her%20payments.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20would%20still%20have%20debt%2C%20and%20I'd%20probably%20be%20way%20more%20burned%20out%20if%20I%20didn't%20take%20a%20break%20and%20come%20back%20focused%20and%20ready%20to%20pay%20off%20my%20debt%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BEverybody%20needs%20a%20break%20sometimes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Credit%20Karma's%20survey%2C%20about%20one%20in%20four%20and%20one%20in%20five%20Gen%20Z%20and%20millennials%2C%20respectively%2C%20said%20they%20will%20use%20cash%20from%20a%20travel-specific%20savings%20fund%20to%20pay%20for%20their%20summer%20vacation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20Spencer%2C%20Zakaria%20Karanikos%2C%2025%2C%20is%20one%20of%20them.%20She%20uses%20a%20sinking%20fund%20to%20budget%20for%20travel%20despite%20graduating%20with%20student%20debt%20%E2%80%94%20a%20balance%20of%20which%20currently%20sits%20just%20shy%20of%20%24120%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20she%20would%20put%20her%20vacation%20expenses%20on%20a%20credit%20card%20and%20work%20extra%20shifts%20to%20pay%20it%20off.%20Now%20that%20she%20earns%20more%20in%20her%20post-grad%20job%20%E2%80%94%20%2472%2C000%20annually%20%E2%80%94%20she%20only%20uses%20credit%20cards%20for%20the%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20my%20age%20feel%20this%20pressure%20to%20either%20not%20care%20about%20money%20and%20travel%20because%20they're%20never%20going%20to%20be%20this%20young%20again%2C%20or%20prioritize%20their%20career%20and%20never%20travel%20to%20get%20financially%20ahead%2C%26quot%3B%20Karanikos%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20you%20should%20find%20a%20way%20to%20balance%20both.%20Our%20time%20is%20limited.%20Both%20can%20be%20important.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222300%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Karanikos%20posing%20by%20fountain%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66be358bb4912df3ae1c04db%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221725%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BBuy%20now%2C%20pay%20later%20is%20the%20worst%20thing%20you%20could%20do%20for%20yourself%2C%26quot%3B%20Karanikos%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20basically%20another%20credit%20card%20and%20the%20way%20it's%20marketed%20in%20your%20brain%20makes%20it%20feel%20less%20important%20and%20high-stakes%20than%20a%20credit%20card.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EZakaria%20Karanikos%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOr%2C%20as%20Spencer%20put%20it%2C%20a%20disagreement%20with%20the%20proliferation%20of%20the%20casual%20%26quot%3Btreat%20yourself%26quot%3B%20mentality.%20%26quot%3BYou%20really%20deserve%20it%20when%20you%20save%20for%20it%20and%20earn%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20she%20no%20longer%20struggles%20with%20the%20urge%20to%20spend%20more%20than%20she%20can%20budget%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20springtime%20Florida%20trip%20almost%20completely%20emptied%20her%20travel%20fund.%20For%20her%2030th%20birthday%20in%20July%2C%20she%20was%20tempted%20to%20put%20another%20trip%20on%20her%20card.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20having%20a%20full%20battle%20with%20myself%2C%20even%20if%20it's%20just%20a%20few%20thousand%20dollars%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20(She%20ultimately%20decided%20against%20it.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpencer%20said%20she%20doesn't%20judge%20people%20who%20put%20vacations%20on%20their%20credit%20cards.%20Of%20course%2C%20she's%20been%20there%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20now%2C%20she%20%26quot%3Bsleeps%20peacefully.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20live%20life%20in%20a%20delusion%2C%20put%20everything%20on%20credit%2C%20and%20hope%20you're%20going%20to%20get%20rich%20or%20pay%20it%20off%20somehow%2C%26quot%3B%20Spencer%20said.%20%26quot%3BEventually%2C%20it%20catches%20up%20with%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-gen-z-travel