e%20for%20people%20with%20disabilities%3F%20As%20a%2020-year-old%2C%20she%20was%20infuriated.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20parents%20encouraged%20me%20to%20write%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20or%20the%20Chief%20Minister%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recalls%20with%20a%20smile.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20her%20earliest%20initiatives%20was%20a%20project%20called%20%E2%80%98Give%20Some%20Space%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20she%20launched%20with%20her%20friend%20Vishal%20Sawvaant%2C%20a%20wheelchair%20user.%20Together%2C%20they%20installed%20ramps%20on%20SB%20Road%2C%20Fergusson%20College%20Road%2C%20and%20nearby%20areas%20in%20Pune%2C%20making%20it%20easier%20for%20wheelchair%20users%20to%20access%20bookstores%2C%20restaurants%2C%20and%20educational%20institutions.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20lived%20reality%20of%20wheelchair%20users%20is%20so%20ignored%20that%20they%20often%20don%E2%80%99t%20even%20have%20the%20option%20to%20visit%20a%20college%20to%20inquire%20about%20admission%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20points%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20Sweta%20and%20her%20cousin%20Nalini%20Mangwani%20created%20an%20art%20installation%20called%20the%20Restroom%20Project.%20The%20artwork%20depicted%20a%20map%20of%20restaurants%20in%20Pune%20on%20a%20cardboard%20canvas%20painted%20with%20bright%20blue%20strokes.%20The%20map%20included%20landmarks%20shaped%20like%20toilet%20seats%20to%20illustrate%20the%20challenges%20of%20finding%20disability-friendly%20restrooms.%20Opening%20each%20commode%20lid%20on%20the%20canvas%20revealed%20whether%20the%20restaurant%20was%20accessible%20by%20people%20with%20disabilities%2C%20whether%20there%20were%20steps%20to%20the%20restroom%20or%20other%20relevant%20features.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20how%20she%20sees%20her%20comedy%20progressing%2C%20Sweta%20says%20that%20there%20are%20many%20aspects%20of%20her%20life%20that%20she%E2%80%99s%20yet%20to%20figure%20out%2C%20including%20nuances%20of%20living%20with%20a%20disability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20definit